<br>
Right now, i just multiply the DW% times the average dammage of my offhand weapon.  However, I have heard that the DW% check occurs every time the primary hand weapon attempts to strike (ie, its based on primary hand delay).<br>
<br>
I hear people all the time shout out, off hand percentage is meaningless!  Put the fastest weapon on primary and highest dammage weapon on secondary.  Does anyone know this to be true or false?<br>
If its false, then I need to change my off hand aggregate dammage from (Basically):<br>
((OH Wep Dmg * (WS+Str)/100)*(1+DA%)/OH Wep Del)*10*DW%<br>
<br>
to<br>
<br>
((OH Wep Dmg * (WS+Str)/100)*(1 + DA%)/(PH Wep Del/DW%))*10<br>
<br>
OH=Off Hand<br>
PH=Primary Hand<br>
WS=Weapon Skill<br>
Str=Strength<br>
DA%=Double Attack%<br>
DW%=Dual Wield %<br>
<br>
I really have no idea which way to do the calcs.  I just got my epic, so these calculations are starting to become important.<br>
<br>
Please note, i dont do modals, as you cant really use them to properly compare two 1 hand weapons to a 2 hand weapon. <p> <a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=46040
